# Copy to `.env` (git-ignored) on alcatraz and fill in the value, then
# `docker compose up -d` from this directory. NEVER commit the real .env.
#
# ACCESS_TOKEN — a GitHub credential with self-hosted-runner REGISTRATION
# rights on gjcourt/homelab. Registration requires repo-admin permission;
# `Contents: read/write` is NOT enough. Pick one:
#   * Classic PAT (simplest): `repo` scope (full).
#   * Fine-grained PAT (preferred): scoped to gjcourt/homelab only, with
#     `Administration: Read and write` + `Metadata: Read-only`.
#   * GitHub App installation token: `Administration: write` + `Metadata: read`.
#
# This is effectively a root-on-alcatraz credential (the runner mounts the
# Docker socket). Store it masked, rotate it like a privileged secret, and do
# NOT reuse the rsync `truenas-backup` key (separation of duties).
ACCESS_TOKEN=ghp_replace_me
